  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200&deg;C/ 180&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7</p>\r\n<p>Grate the <strong>cheddar cheese&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Drain the&nbsp;<strong>tuna</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>grated cheese</strong>, <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong>, <strong>drained tuna</strong> and <strong>egg<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> to a large bowl with a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Knead&nbsp;the <strong>tuna mix</strong> with clean hands for 1 min or until smooth</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1144.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1144.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1144.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1144.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1144.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Divide the<strong> tuna mix</strong> into 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4] </span>and shape<span class=\"text-danger\">&nbsp;</span>into patties and refrigerate until later</p>\r\n<p>Put the patties in the freezer to firm up</p>\r\n<p>Tip: if the mixture is too wet, add some flour</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1144.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1144.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1144.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1144.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1144.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut the<strong> sweet potatoes</strong> (skins on) into <strong>chips</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>chips</strong> to a large baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong>&nbsp;and give everything a good mix up&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Put the tray in the oven for 25-30 min or until the <strong>chips</strong> are golden and starting to crisp</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1144.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1144.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1144.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1144.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1144.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and slice the <strong>shallot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> finely</p>\r\n<p>Combine the <strong>red wine vinegar</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> in a small bowl&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once the<strong> sugar </strong>has&nbsp;dissolved, add the<strong> sliced shallot</strong> and set aside &ndash; this is your<strong> pickled shallot</strong></p>",
